# Keep shell and Python scripts LF-only, even on Windows clones where
# core.autocrlf=true would otherwise rewrite them to CRLF. Bash chokes on
# CRLF ("python3^M: command not found", "set: -\r: invalid option"), so this
# is the first thing that breaks on Windows without it. No-op on Unix.
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
